step_data.thought:
I've been zooming in on the map by clicking the 'Zoom In' button (bid '406') six times now. Looking at the current state of the page, I can see from the URL that we're now at zoom level 12 (as shown in the URL 'map=12/42.8960/-75.1080').

In OpenStreetMap, data export functionality typically becomes available at higher zoom levels, usually around zoom level 13-14 or higher. This is because exporting large areas at lower zoom levels would be too resource-intensive.

The 'Zoom In' link (bid '406') is still available and currently focused, so I should continue clicking it to increase the zoom level further. I'll click it again to get closer to the required zoom level for data export.
